==Finnish==
{{Finnish index|ol}}

===Etymology===

See Estonian [[olla#Estonian|olla]].

===Verb===
'''olla'''

#to [[be]]
#to [[exist]] ([[olla olemassa]])

====Conjugation====

Only the [[indicative]] present tense has an irregular form, and the stem is just ''o-'' in the third person plural. The [[potential]] mood is formed from another stem, ''[[lie-]]'', in its active forms.

<table border="1">
<tr><th>&nbsp;    </th><th>indicative present</th><th>potential present</th></tr>
<tr><td>(minä)</td><td>olen  </td><td>lienen</td></tr>
<tr><td>(sinä)</td><td>olet  </td><td>lienet</td></tr>
<tr><td>hän   </td><td>on    </td><td>lienee</td></tr>
<tr><td>(me)  </td><td>olemme</td><td>lienemme</td></tr>
<tr><td>(te)  </td><td>olette</td><td>lienette</td></tr>
<tr><td>he    </td><td>ovat  </td><td>lienevät</td></tr>
<tr><td>''impersonal''</td><td>ollaan</td><td>oltaneen</td></tr>
</table>

